  (new-hardblocks-found
    (HARDBLOCK-21
      :severity HIGH
      :owner ada
      :location "scheme-books/book-of-ml/16-the-tiny-llm.book.slatl (multiple locations 444-455, 693-703, and others)"
      :description "Ch 16 has 6-8 bare ``` fences containing math derivations (∂L/∂z[i] = ...), pseudocode (pre = W1 * ln2_x + b1), and expected output (iter 0 loss 3.02). These are indistinguishable from Scheme fences to any extractor. Whole-chapter run-all would fail with `unbound symbol: ∂L/∂z[i]`."
      :evidence "extracted all 32 fenced blocks; 6 are non-Scheme content; ./bin/motoi run on setup blocks 1-8 succeeds; block 9 (∂L/∂z[i] = ...) breaks with `unbound symbol: ∂L/∂z[i]`"
      :fix "tag math/pseudocode/output fences with `text` or `math`, and make extractor filter on scheme tag OR use indented text instead of fences for non-code")

    (HARDBLOCK-22
      :severity MEDIUM
      :owner marcus
